OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1779207074
OL,3,CPlaid Cymru ramp up the push for more
OL,4,Cpowers for Wales
OL,6,FPlaid Cymru has formed a minority
OL,7,Fgovernment in Cardiff after becoming
OL,8,Fthe largest party in the Senedd
OL,9,Ffollowing the election on May 7th.
OL,11,FLast week, Rhun ap Iorwerth became the
OL,12,Ffirst non-Labour First Minister since
OL,13,Fthe devolved era began in 1999.
OL,15,FHe also appointed his cabinet which
OL,16,Fwill meet for the first time this
OL,17,Fweek. He'll also deliver a statement
OL,18,Fon his priorities in a first plenary
OL,19,Fmeeting of the Senedd.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/13
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1779207074
OL,3,CPlaid Cymru ramp up the push for more
OL,4,Cpowers for Wales
OL,6,FIt's no surprise that Plaid Cymru has
OL,7,Falso moved quickly to begin its
OL,8,Fargument for further powers, having
OL,9,Fpromised in its manifesto that it will
OL,10,Fseek to "reset the relationship
OL,11,Fbetween the Welsh and UK Governments."
OL,13,FAccording to the Welsh Government, in
OL,14,Fhis call with Keir Starmer, Rhun ap
OL,15,FIorwerth "made clear he will wish to
OL,16,Fnegotiate on the Barnett formula, fair
OL,17,Ffunding, borrowing powers, rail and
OL,18,Ffurther devolution.
OL,26,@rD@IOUsD@fO]wD@JOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/13
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1779207074
OL,3,CPlaid Cymru ramp up the push for more
OL,4,Cpowers for Wales
OL,6,F"The First Minister noted that a
OL,7,FSenedd majority, including the Labour
OL,8,Fgroup, is in favour of enhanced powers.
OL,10,F"The Prime Minister confirmed that he
OL,11,Fwould be open to a conversation on
OL,12,Fpowers relating to devolution and
OL,13,Fproposed an in-person meeting in June
OL,14,Fwith the first ministers of Scotland
OL,15,Fand Northern Ireland to discuss issues
OL,16,Fof relevance."
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUxD@NO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/13
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
