FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1779207074
OL,3,CPlaid Cymru ramp up the push for more
OL,4,Cpowers for Wales
OL,6,FPlaid Cymru's Westminster leader Liz
OL,7,FSaville Roberts said that "It was
OL,8,Fdisappointing that the King's Speech
OL,9,Ffailed to match the people of Wales's
OL,10,Fappetite for major change. Plaid Cymru
OL,11,Fhas tabled an amendment to the King's
OL,12,FSpeech calling for a new Wales Bill in
OL,13,Fwhich we will set out why and how
OL,14,Fstronger powers and fair funding for
OL,15,Four nation are necessary to bring
OL,16,Fabout the change Wales needs.
OL,26,@oD@[OU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G8/13
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1779207074
OL,3,CPlaid Cymru ramp up the push for more
OL,4,Cpowers for Wales
OL,6,F"If Keir Starmer is serious about
OL,7,Fbeing 'open' to discussing more powers
OL,8,Ffor Wales, then his Government should
OL,9,Flisten to our demands for a new Wales
OL,10,FBill. The people of Wales have sent
OL,11,FWestminster a clear message ` you
OL,12,Fcannot ignore our voices any longer."
OL,14,FOther parties have also already begun
OL,15,Fcriticising Plaid Cymru's approach.
OL,16,FReform UK's leader in Wales, Dan
OL,17,FThomas said that ""We will scrutinise
OL,18,Ftheir actions and work to ensure that
OL,19,Ftheir attention is on our public
OL,20,Fservices and not Welsh independence."
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@eO]yD@ROUyD@SOU|D@eO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G9/13
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
